# Testing Standards

Apply to every code change or bug fix. Goal: write/adjust tests and keep coverage meaningful.

## Runner
- Use Jest (`pnpm test`).  
- Config in `jest.config.js`.  
- Setup in `jest.setup.js` (jsdom, mocks).

## Placement
- Co-locate tests under `__tests__` or as `*.test.ts(x)` next to the code.

## Types of Tests
- **Unit:** components, hooks, use cases. Mock network with `whatwg-fetch`/MSW.  
- **Integration:** Next.js route handlers in `app/api/**` with mocked dependencies.

## Snapshots
- Keep snapshots small and stable.  
- Prefer explicit assertions over large snapshots.

## Fixtures & Mocks
- Use Testing Library patterns.  
- Avoid deep mocking—test behavior over implementation details.

## Coverage
- Maintain or improve current coverage.  
- Do not remove meaningful tests without replacement.

## Performance
- Tests must run fast locally and in CI.  
- Prefer deterministic tests; avoid real sleeps or external networks.

## Preflight
- Lint and typecheck must be green alongside tests.

## Documentation
- Update `docs/Testing.md` when conventions or helpers change.
